Sebastian Ferreira notched a goal and two assists and Steve Clark turned away all nine shots he faced as the Houston Dynamo cruised to a 3-0 victory over the Galaxy on Sunday. Ferreira staked the Dynamo (5-5-3) to an early lead with a goal in the 11th minute. Ferreira notched assists in the second half on goals by Tyler Pasher in the 58th minute and Thorleifur Ulfarsson in the 62nd.  The Galaxy (6-5-2) outshot the Dynamo 16-13 and had a 9-8 edge in shots on goal. Jonathan Bond stopped five of the eight shots he faced for the Galaxy. 